etymologies: early 17th century: apparently from the rare adjective dump ‘of the consistency of dough’, although dumpling is recorded much earlier

definitions: a small savory ball of dough (usually made with suet) which may be boiled, fried, or baked in a casserole.
shortDefinitions: small savoury ball of dough usually made with suet which may be boiled, fried, or baked in casserole

definitions: (in East Asian cuisine) a small item of food consisting of a thin sheet of dough wrapped around a savory filling and cooked by steaming or frying.
shortDefinitions: East Asian food consisting of thin sheet of dough wrapped around savoury filling

definitions: a dessert consisting of apples or other fruit enclosed in a sweet dough and baked.
shortDefinitions: pudding consisting of fruit enclosed in sweet dough
